attributes.name: active
attributes.description: Determines whether the counter is visible or not
attributes.name: day-month
attributes.description: The content that is placed in the month space in the `week` or `month` view. The day & time object is passed through this slots scope.

attributes.name: event
attributes.description: The content placed in an event. This ignores the `event-name` prop.

attributes.name: color
attributes.description: Applies specified color to the control - it can be the name of material color (for example `success` or `purple`) or css color (`#033` or `rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)`). You can find a list of built-in classes on the [colors page](/styles/colors#material-colors).

attributes.name: dark
attributes.description: Applies the dark theme variant to the component. You can find more information on the Material Design documentation for [dark themes](https://material.io/design/color/dark-theme.html).

attributes.name: day-format
attributes.description: Formats day of the month string that appears in a day to a specified locale

attributes.name: end
attributes.description: The ending date on the calendar (inclusive) in the format of `YYYY-MM-DD`. This may be ignored depending on the `type` of the calendar.

attributes.name: first-interval
attributes.description: The first interval to display in the `day` view. If `intervalMinutes` is set to 60 and this is set to 9 the first time in the view is 9am.

attributes.name: first-time
attributes.description: The first time to display in the `day` view. If specified, this overwrites any `firstInterval` value specified. This can be the number of minutes since midnight, a string in the format of `HH:mm`, or an object with number properties hour and minute.

attributes.name: hide-header
attributes.description: If the header at the top of the `day` view should be visible.

attributes.name: interval-count
attributes.description: The number of intervals to display in the `day` view.

attributes.name: interval-format
attributes.description: Formats time of day string that appears in the interval gutter of the `day` and `week` view to specified locale

attributes.name: interval-height
attributes.description: The height of an interval in pixels in the `day` view.

attributes.name: interval-minutes
attributes.description: The number of minutes the intervals are in the `day` view. A common interval is 60 minutes so the intervals are an hour.

attributes.name: interval-style
attributes.description: Returns CSS styling to apply to the interval.

attributes.name: interval-width
attributes.description: The width of the interval gutter on the left side in the `day` view.

attributes.name: light
attributes.description: Applies the light theme variant to the component.

attributes.name: locale
attributes.description: The locale of the calendar.

attributes.name: max-days

v-mutate
slots.description: By default takes a function that is invoked when user clicks outside of the element the directive is attached to. It can also be an object, which allows you to provide `closeConditional` and `include` callbacks.
slots.name: Intersect
once
slots.description: Will only invoke the provided user callback once, then directive will be unbound.
slots.name: attr
slots.description: Sets the value of [attributes](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MutationObserverInit/attributes) to true.
slots.name: char
slots.description: Sets the value of [characterData](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MutationObserverInit/characterData) to true.
slots.name: child
slots.description: Sets the value of [childList](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MutationObserverInit/childList) to true.
slots.name: sub
slots.description: Sets the value of [subtree](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MutationObserver/observe#Parameters) to true.
slots.name: v-intersect
slots.description: By default takes a handler function that is invoked when the element that the directive is attached to enters or leaves the visible browser area. It can also take an object, which allows you to pass along [IntersectionObserver options](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/IntersectionObserver/IntersectionObserver).
slots.name: once
slots.description: The provided handler function is only invoked once, the first time the element is visible.
slots.name: quiet
slots.description: Will not invoke the handler function if the element is visible when the IntersectionObserver is created.
Will only invoke the provided user callback on mount and once intersected. If using the **quiet** modifier will only invoke once.
slots.name: quiet
slots.description: Will not automatically invoke the provided callback on bind.
slots.name: Mutate
v-ripple
slots.description: By default takes a handler function that is invoked when the element that the directive is attached to is mutated. It can also take an object, which allows you to pass along [MutationObserver options](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MutationObserver/observe).

slots.name: char

slots.name: child
slots.description: See `childList` option [here](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MutationObserver/observe).
slots.name: sub

slots.name: once
slots.description: The provided handler function is only invoked once.
slots.name: immediate
slots.description: The provided handler function is invoked immediately when directive is attached to element.
slots.name: Resize
v-resize
slots.description: The provided handler function will be invoked each time the browser window is resized.
slots.name: active
slots.description: By default the resize event listener is added to window with the `passive` option. This modifier sets `passive` to **false**.
slots.name: quiet
slots.description: By default the provided handler function is invoked once when the directive is attached to the element. This modifier disabled that behavior.
slots.name: quiet
slots.description: Will **not** automatically invoke the provided callback on bind.
slots.name: Ripple
v-scroll
slots.description: A boolean can be used to control if the ripple directive should be active or not. You can provide an object with a `class` property to have that class applied to the ripple container element.
slots.name: center
slots.description: Makes it so that the ripple originates from the center of the element, instead where the user clicked on it.
slots.name: circle
slots.description: Changes the ripple behavior to better match circular elements.
slots.name: stop
slots.description: Prevents ripples from being triggered on any other elements when the click event is bubbling up.
slots.name: #target
slots.description: The target watched for scroll changes. Defaults to window but can be changed to any valid id selector.
slots.name: self
slots.description: Binds to the element that the the directive is attached.
slots.name: Scroll
v-touch
slots.description: By default takes a handler function that is invoked whenever the target of the directive is scrolled. It can also take an object, which allows you to pass along event listener options as described [here](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget/addEventListener).
slots.name: self
slots.description: By default the scroll event listener is attached to the argument provided to the directive, interpreted as a query selector. If no argument is provided then it is attached to the window object. If this modifier is used then it is instead attached to the element the directive is used on.
slots.name: Touch
v-click-outside
slots.description: The value is always an object. The `start`, `end`, `move`, `left`, `right`, `up` and `down` functions can be used to invoke a function when the corresponding touch action occurs. If the `parent` option attaches the touch listeners to the parent element instead of the element the directive is used on. The `options` object is described [here](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget/addEventListener).
